sudo apt install curl
Download the Node.js 18.16.0 binary distribution for Linux by running the following command:

bash
Copy code
curl -o node-v18.16.0-linux-x64.tar.xz https://nodejs.org/dist/v18.16.0/node-v18.16.0-linux-x64.tar.xz
Extract the downloaded archive using the following command:

Copy code
tar -xvf node-v18.16.0-linux-x64.tar.xz
Copy the extracted files to the /usr/local directory:

bash
Copy code
sudo cp -r node-v18.16.0-linux-x64/* /usr/local/
Verify that Node.js is installed correctly by running:

Copy code
node -v
